

1) The /proc/interrupts file is used to check IRQs being used on the system.

Correct
Correct answer

True

2) Which command will allow you to see the status of modules in the Linux Kernel?

Correct
Correct answer

lsmod

3) The grub configuration file is located at:

Correct
Correct answer

/boot/grub/menu.lst

4) What information is contained in the /proc/dma file?

Correct
Correct answer

which dma channels are currently in use by the system

5) The lspci command can display details about all of the following except for:

Correct
Correct answer

Ethernet card MAC addresses
